This paper deals with network traffic estimation and anomaly detection, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of convex and non-convex optimization techniques, which are common in the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of spatiotemporal correlation and Bayesian approaches, which are relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
